Insurance companies face data sprawl with disparate systems and¬error-prone manual processes impeding a holistic view of the business and risk exposure. Gaining this insight is critical at a time when the regulatory environment demands businesses improve their risk models and practices.

Using actuarial statistical analysis and modelling based upon Microsoft solutions, insurance companies are able to better identify risks, price¬policies more effectively, understand their liabilities more accurately,¬and optimise their financial positions.

As the pace of global financial services accelerates and speed becomes essential to decision-making, traditional tools are simply too slow. Coupled with massive on-premises server farms being unsustainably expensive, there is a real need for higher computing throughput but with a compelling TCO.

Microsoft analytics solutions enable financial institutions to benefit from cloud computing by reducing capex and facilitating more complex data analysis. Typical scenarios include risk computation and modelling plus predictive analytics through machine learning of data analysis & patterns.

Faced with exponentially increasing volumes of data, it is challenging for financial institutions to translate that data into insight needed to improve customer profitability and retention. To do this effectively, you need deeper insight into the profitability of you customer portfolio and have the ability to visualise that data so it is actionable.

With Microsoft customer and product analytics solutions, you can capitalise on internal and external data to combine profitability, segmentation and customer preference, to gain a complete end-to-end view of the customer.

¬Microsoft has pioneered reference architecture frameworks for industries such as upstream oil and gas operations (MURA), smart energy and water (SERA), discrete manufacturing (DIRA) and chemical and oil refining (ChemRA).  They are Industry-validated and provide guidance on addressing technology challenges and developments. SERA provides an end-to-end reference architecture for an integrated utilities company.

¬Microsoft platforms incorporate an advanced security model for controlling access to data.  'Role based' privileges ensure users can only perform actions relevant to them.  With access so easily controlled, it's easy to segment responsibilities for analysing and extracting insights from data, across many different industry scenarios and including your partner organisations.

Large amounts of data can provide very powerful insights but these are only useful when everyone is using the same, correct, base data. Microsoft can help to ensure all insight is being driven from a single, agreed source or set of sources, allowing you to have complete confidence in the insight gained.

With Power BI for Office 365 you can query data using natural language and see almost-instantaneous results in the form of interactive visualisations. The Q&A feature, guides users on questions to ensure answers match the question intent.  Best practices can also improve the quality of the answers.

A closed loop view of data, across all touch points within an organisation, provides a single view of the customer.  Payment history, service challenges, marketing strategies that have provided value and details on tariffs can all be tracked using the Microsoft Dynamics CRM platform.  Regardless of the channels a customer uses to communicate, any CRM user can know the customer, transforming the customer experience.

¬If a customer has paid late for the last three quarters or if a particular address shows a pattern of late payments, (despite different tenants) it's reasonable to consider payments may continue to be late.¬Microsoft's analytics tools make it easy to identify these patterns and provide the insights to connect with customers to help with payment options or offer ways of reducing consumption.

Microsoft's powerful analytics and insights tools help to understand buying behaviours, preferences and what customers value the most.  Data is actionable, supporting decisions with tangible evidence.  With a better understanding of customers, experiences can be more personal and relevant, driving customer loyalty.

There is no longer one single way in which all customers want to interact with a supplier. To ensure customer loyalty and improve customer satisfaction it is important to offer relevant ways for customers to interact with your company. Increasingly this is driving towards mobile and social-based methods of communication and Microsoft can help with this transition.

Addressing equipment challenges proactively requires current status data that's easy to access and interpret.  Equipment represented visually on a Microsoft Bing map with drill down ability, supported by the Internet of Things, ensures staff are always aware of the current technology estate situation.  It's possible to 'watch' performance degrade and forecast a response which also improves maintenance efficiency, reducing costs.

Management of plant technology can be improved by a consolidated view across multiple plants.  With Microsoft's actionable insights tools and role-based control, it's possible to engage 3rd parties to oversee an equipment estate view, making informed decisions that further improve uptime and reduce costs.

Optimise production, maintain safety and maximise the petroleum recovery of reserves by delivering tactical, operational, and strategic insights to everyone in the organisation based on their job role.  Microsoft solutions create a more intelligent organisation by using data streamed from connected sensors and devices as well as combining it with actionable analytics to help optimise production, improve maintenance, and drive higher profitability.
Responding to outages requires fast and intuitive access to data about equipment, infrastructure and networks, especially when you want to tell the customer about an outage before they tell you.

Microsoft's insights technology ensures information is current, relevant and can be shared with 3rd parties in a controlled way.  The right assistance can be engaged and provided with an informed view to address challenges seamlessly and quickly.
